<div class='commentbox'>
I was informed by my fellow climbers that they built a bridge over little clear where the climbing<br/>
trail crosses the river towards the confluence with clear creek. They did not know that people<br/>
kayak that river. The bridge is made with pretty big logs and was built when clear creek was at<br/>
around 1500cfs, so hopefully it will be washed down with higher flows and won't turn into a<br/>
strainer. So keep that in mind when running the little clear. </div>
