<div class='commentinfo comment_'>
2005-01-17 11:05:37 (3421 days ago)
<div id='contact-5059'><span class='name'>Karl Whipp</span><span class='send-message'><a href="/content/Contact/view/contactid/5059/display/detail/">Details</a></span></div> </div>
<div class='commentbox'>
Checking the Level: Walk straight down the left side of the bridge. You will see a small footpath<br/>
leading straight down to the creek. Carry a paddle down with you. From the edge of the creek where<br/>
the footpath ends, you want to have a full paddle blade in depth for a minimum level. When I say<br/>
this, I mean that it has to cover the ENTIRE blade and should be lapping up on the shaft itself.<br/>
Again, this is a good minimum level, but an inch or two can make all the difference on this run. </div>
</td>
</tr>
